                <td bgColor="#0A0634"><textarea cols="48" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL" onselect="storeCaret(this);" onclick="storeCaret(this);" onkeyup="storeCaret(this);" onchange="storeCaret(this);">[quote][i]Originally posted by Avoozl[/i]
[br]Wandering through some posts about the efficiency of Lich/Lifetap combos, I came across an interesting one where the person said that if your regen was greater than the amount of damage you were taking on a tick from liching, you do NOT get the 66/75% bonus but instead take full damage.

So I played around with that this morning and found that yes, it seemed to be true for the 29 LoT/20 AoD combo at least.

I checked through the archives and found a few posts that hinted that this was true, but no actual confirmation.

So:  Two parts to my question.
1)  Is this true?  I assume it is, but I'd like confirmation from higher level/more experienced necros than myself.

2)  If so, then is it common practice to click off lich while a lifetap is ongoing, to get the absolute maximum health/mana conversion, or is it even worth your while to do so?

Any answers would be appreciated.

