r />So Lich took 32hp per tick.<br /><br />So there seems to be a factor here that everyone is missing. <br />But, sadly, it DOES appear that if the spell heal (not counting natural regen) is around at least %66 greater than the hp drain that our pact/lich line of spells are doing, that the PvP damage nerf does not take effect and it does the full amount of damage.<br /><br />I'm not sure why the Lich example came up for 26hp drain for Leach and 29hp drain for VC though. Maybe some weird formula verant threw in there that we will never know..<br /><br />It would be interesting to see what people come up with for our higher level lich spells (as I don't have them yet), and Allure of Death with the above chart.. I'm too tired to mess with AoD for now. <img src="images/ashamed_125.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /></span></font></td>
